00:00:00,720 --> 00:00:06,320
A report is related to the article, but is often more painting.

2
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:11,120
Use environmental descriptions: how it smells, feels and looks.

3
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:15,640
Everything that feels relevant to creating a scenario.

4
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:22,640
With an attractive preamble, you arouse interest in the reader to read more.

5
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:26,480
Tips to think about:

6
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:32,800
Choose where your focus is.
 How can you best tell us what you want to say?

7
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:38,080
Choose the environment and people to interview that feel relevant.

8
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:49,800
It is good to record the interview and listen to it afterwards.

9
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:54,720
Write down support words to more easily find in your interview.

10
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:59,600
Experiment with the rhythm.
 Mix long and short sentences.

11
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:04,440
Vary the language.
 It creates a tension in the reading.

